### VM Orchestrator Service
# @baseUrl = http://localhost:8080

### Check Health
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Root info
GET {{baseUrl}}/

# ============ VM PROVISIONING ============

### Provision VM with VM Class ID (Recommended)
POST {{baseUrl}}/provision
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <token>

{
  "template_id": 1,
  "manual_value": "proyecto1",
  "vcenter_datacenter": "DC01",
  "vcenter_cluster": "Cluster01",
  "vcenter_resource_pool": "Production",
  "vm_class_id": 1
}

### Provision VM with custom specs (no VM Class)
POST {{baseUrl}}/provision
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <token>

{
  "template_id": 1,
  "manual_value": "customvm",
  "vcenter_datacenter": "DC01",
  "vcenter_cluster": "Cluster01",
  "vcenter_resource_pool": "Development",
  "specs": {
    "cpu": 4,
    "ram": 8192,
    "storage": 200,
    "cpu_reservation_percent": 25,
    "ram_reservation_percent": 25,
    "provisioning_type": "thin",
    "storage_policy": "Silver-Policy"
  }
}

### Provision VM with VM Class + override some specs
POST {{baseUrl}}/provision
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <token>

{
  "template_id": 1,
  "manual_value": "customoverride",
  "vcenter_datacenter": "DC01",
  "vcenter_cluster": "Cluster01",
  "vcenter_resource_pool": "Production",
  "vm_class_id": 1,
  "specs": {
    "storage": 1000
  }
}

# ============ STATUS CHECK ============

### Check provisioning status
GET {{baseUrl}}/status/<job-id>
